The paper deals with inferring individual attributes from search engine queries, which is a classic information retrieval problem. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves statistical analysis and machine learning techniques, which are common in sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing), and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper discusses privacy concerns and anonymization techniques, which are relevant to the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
